<br>
This weekend made me really just not understand shadowknights at all.<br>
<br>
Sure, it seemd to be that mostly it was two people and they coulda just been dumb, but it also seems to be a growing trend.<br>
<br>
Shadowknights who do not want to help the main tank keep agro.<br>
<br>
Two situations came up. The first was at a raid. The MT (not me I was SA) was having some problems keeping agro on the mobs we were clearing. So I asked our highest level shadow knight to give him his best hate/agro spell. The shadow knight refused saying he didn't want to cause of the recast time. Note that the spell in the voice line lasts 10 minutes and has a 9 minute recast time and it is damn effective.<br>
<br>
We had 2 CR's cause of a mob ping ponging to the casters cause of this. Eventually, the MA got down hard on that SK and got the buff and things were ok after that.<br>
<br>
My second experience was last night in the plane of storms. <br>
My group (war, cleric, shaman, paladin, mage then later ranger, and the sk) decided that since I had some 700 more hps and 100 more ac I should be the MT in the group since we had 3 tanks. I asked the SK for the voice line, he refused saying he didn't want to switch out one of his other spells.<br>
<br>
Now this guy had other problems like pulling when the cleric says not to and not FD'ing stuff off so he could live. <br>
We were fighting some tough yellow con mobs and the guy said he would just tank since I couldn't pull agro off him.<br>
<br>
He ended up dying several times due to not managing his agro. (Paladin didn't have a problem letting me have agro and they can out agro me any day of the week). All he needed to do was to FD (yeah I know it is a spell with a cast time) or give me the voice line and he would have lived. Instead he accused the cleric and shaman of being incompetant for not healing him. I would have been happy letting him tank if he had comparable hit points and ac fully buffed. But he didn't and the group wanted me to tank because of it. I eventually told my friends in tells and say (when he died) that this guy was no good and left after our second CR due to him(it was bedtime anyhow).<br>
<br>
I have met some really great sk's who know what they are doing and who watch their agro if they aren't supposed to be tanking. <br>
<br>
But I leave this as a bit of a warning. Be wary of SK's who refuse to cast the voice line on the MT, be it you or them or anyone else. They may result in CR's and exp loss.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Aveen Lucenthawk<br>
Half Elven Warlord of 61 Battles<br>
