The biggest pain about the Voice line for SK's is that darned refresh time; and admittedly I mumble to myself when I have to load it too.  There's also a bug or timing issue with the Voice line where it 'ungreys' but it's still uncastable.<br>
<br>
However, it is effective and does make aggro management easier (IMO).  I get mad at myself when I don't think of memming it in time (say before a raid/encounter) or if I get asked late to cast it on someone (I rarely use it on myself) and it's not memmed yet.<br>
<br>
If I'm not MA, I generally don't mind memming it at all (after my initial mumbles, that is) because I won't need whatever spell which was in the slot that is now occupied by the Voice spell.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't go as far myself to say those were 'bad' SK's; but would venture to say that they may not have done what was best for the group. <p><p>[64 Grave Lord] Duke <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=170915 ">Klotar</A> (Dark Elf)<BR>
