<br>
<br>
I think perhaps this warrior didn't understand.<br>
<br>
Both SK and Paladin HAVE a taunt button.. and a lower cap.  We are well aware of how the taunt button works... (or in some cases doesn't) we are also quite aware of the margin for error.<br>
<br>
SK can give and lose aggro on command (mana allowing).  Paladins taunt on command.  Both classes when they have experienced players behind them are head and shoulders above most warrior's understanding of taunt because we understand and practice both the melee(taunt button) and the spell casting half of aggro.  <br>
<br>
In addition, SK are among the game's best pullers and most of the older ones understand a great deal about mob interaction due to their involvement in high end pull teams their whole EQ life.  I agree that there are twits playing all classes... but for the most part knight required playstyles teach their players much more about aggro than a warrior (who only plays a warrior 60+) might ever understand.<br>
<br>
We all know ebay is bad.  This is why there is this little button called &quot;disband&quot;.<br>
<br>
<br>
The point being made here is that a Shadowknight(or Paladin) and a warrior working TOGETHER to give the warrior aggro means the warrior will have an immense advantage.<br>
<br>
Example:<br>
SK_01 pulls mob_01 with Terror of Terris (510 hate unresistable)<br>
SK_01 brings back to camp and casts a Darkness spell (damage+snare) on the mob.<br>
Warrior_01 presses the Taunt button and gets the SK's hate +1<br>
SK_01 feigns death<br>
Warrior_01 is now 1000+ hate over everyone..  the SK falls below the warrior by being down...  The SK stands up and manages aggro.<br>
<br>
Paladins can do the same thing by passing aggro with distance modifiers and intelligent aggro management on both parts.<br>
<br>
Now, if only I could get more warriors to grab onto this!<br>
<br>
<br>
I usually politely ask other tanks in the party their HP/AC and let the cleric decide...  There are parties where the warrior should be tank all the time...  and then there are parties where the warrior should never hit the taunt button.<br>
<br>
A good player knows when these times are, and knows when and where to offer their support.<br>
<br>
Example #1<br>
Warrior_01 decides they will be main tank and the party goes along with it.. despite the fact I am 2 levels higher and have the same HP and AC as he does.  I give him voice and carefully avoid aggro until the chanter and cleric are respectively getting chapped.  I uber taunt BOTH mobs on to me and call for ASSIST.  The cleric heals me and we survive.  I am elected MT.  The warrior pitches a fit, but the cleric (and chanter) try to convince him that this is best.  Warrior_01 quits the group despite the fact no one asked him to leave (and we really didn't want to look for another melee.)<br>
<br>
Example #2<br>
Warrior_02 is elected MT.  He has more HP and 3 levels on me.  He gets voice and I pull.  I feign and he tags.. works good until we meet Named_01 who the warrior just cant seem to stick to him.  We wipe (partially due to incoming mini-train gifted to us)  I recommend that I tank the named as I will be able to glue it to me.  I was pleasantly surprised when the warrior yanks out his 2H and backs me up saying &quot;bah it doesn't hit that hard&quot; despite some of the other party member's misgivings.  I am elected to try it... if I die the warrior will take over.  The mob is glued to me... never looks at the chanter or cleric, and it and its guards die easily.<br>
<br>
Warriors and Knights are brothers... we have different strengths... recoginize them and give each other their due.  The game is a lot more fun that way.<br>
<br>
Baazghul &quot;Brik&quot; Bludgaard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=varaho1>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1129<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/02 5:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2497.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: taunt</span><hr size=1> Another thing people have to step away from is this fantasy of tank stacking. Tanking doesn't stack, tanks should be viable on their lonesome for tanking ( IE. w/o too much outside influence ) and have a non-tanking roll. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rani>rani</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/02 8:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2497.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: taunt</span><hr size=1> While I understand the concept of high hybrid taunt in beginning of fight, then warrior taunt, its not always a comfortable way to fight imo, plus its rather unreliable.<br>
<br>
Sure if there is no rogues in the group it can probably work fine because in that case it doesnt matter if the SK/Pally is tanking some of the time, but with a rogue its important that the back is always pointed towards the rogue, or they get cranky when they cant backstab.<br>
<br>
For instance the other day I had the &quot;worst case&quot; scenario group. 1 SK+me(war)+1(obnoxious <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )rogue.<br>
<br>
Was wielding BoC+getting voice from the SK, but even then I would instantly lose agro whenever he snared the mob with Festering Darkness(we were in lower rats in CoD, so needed the snare).<br>
<br>
Of course you could argue that the SK and me should just stand side by side, but thats really a kind of awkard and uncomfortable way to fight in an exp group for hours on end.<br>
<br>
So what usually would happen is I would tank the mob, try to bring it to a wall, then tank it with my own shoulder to the wall. The SK would be attacking facing the mob/wall, and whenever he stole agro, we would hear loud complaints from the rogue because he couldnt backstab.<br>
<br>
In the end it all worked out, because once the rogue left, we didnt really had to position the mob in any particular manner, so with the enchanter that took the rogues place + his DC'ed pet we ended up kicking ass instead, and with alot less hassle of trying to position the mob <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=broddathep>Brodda Thep</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/02 9:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2497.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: taunt</span><hr size=1> I would rather have a pally/sk tank in PoP 90% of the time over a warrior.  <br>
<br>
I group with pet classes a lot so positioning of the mob is important since it is nice if mellee + pet can attack through enrage.  Pallies/SKs can keep agro far better through enrage than a warrior.<br>
<br>
Pallies/SKs tend to use two handers.  If you are dual wielding and tanking a slowed mob you are probably taking fully 30% more damage just from repostes. (I parsed that 60% of the total damage taken over a nights fight when tanking slowed mobs with my monk was from repostes.)  This makes fast weapons crap for taking damage.<br>
<br>
Lucklily, you guys get an awesome AA to hit through repostes and the like.  Unfortunately, not many warriors have this AA yet.<br>
<br>
Also if you are engaging on pull and the mobs can't be rooted it is nice if the tank can build up massive agro before I try to slow with my shaman.  IF I get a resist and the mob comes after me I don't want to hear &quot;Sorry, dude.  Taunt failed will be up in another 5 seconds.&quot;  (or whatever the time on taunt is.)<br>
<br>
In most cases it is better for the hybrid to be tanking in the group.  There are probably exceptions but I would think that an SK would be able to do more damage with spells and what not if he was able to tank, the pally could stun more if he was able to tank and use his healing spells.   And the warrior could also do more damage from behind the mob and even use offensive if he wanted for even more damage.<br>
<br>
Of course if the SK/Pally is just unable to tank the mob then that should be addressed.  But too many times a group will have to reduce their effectiveness in order to allow the warrior to tank when there is a pally/sk in the group.<br>
<br>
Just use whoever would be best for the group to tank.  Don't just think that warriors MUST tank.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=leod>Leod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/02 11:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2497.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: taunt</span><hr size=1> I agree with Brik.<br>
